My Titanic kaggle implementation in python¶

Hi ! Here is a little example of Titanic data analysis, in order to guess if someone survived or not.

It will become cleaner with time, for the moment it's just a start :-)

At first, let's describe data ...

Initialization of Machine Learning Workflow¶

Now we are going to train model on the data, without data transformation. We will use only the few numeric ones.

First, we split the dataset :

In [33]:
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

columns = ["Fare", "Pclass","SibSp","Parch"]

labels = train_df["Survived"].values
features = train_df[list(columns)].values

X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(features, labels, test_size=0.3, random_state=0)

Let's use a fonction to save our models :

In [5]:
import os
from time import gmtime, strftime

def save_model(modelPath=working_directory+'./model/', column_names='error',
               score=0, model='error no model', comments='', logLevel="DEBUG"):
    file_name = modelPath+"results.csv"

    if os.path.exists(file_name):
        append_write = 'a' # append if already exists
    else:
        append_write = 'w' # make a new file if not

    result_file = open(file_name,append_write)
    if append_write == 'w':
        result_file.write("Time;Score;Columns;Model;Comments" + '\n')

    result= strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S", gmtime())+ ';' +str(score)+';'+''.join(map(str, column_names))+';'+''.join(str(model).splitlines())+';'+comments
    result_file.write(result + '\n')
    result_file.close()

    #TODO: it could be nice to store model's training time1

We now add some data in the ML workflow¶

Numeric columns with NA's fields can't be use just like that. We will create some new columns with some NA replacement.

In [44]:
working_directory="C:/Users/Jérémie/IdeaProjects/titanic-kaggle-py/"
train_df = pd.read_csv(open(working_directory+"./data/train.csv", 'r'))
train_df['AgeMed'] = train_df['Age'].fillna((train_df['Age'].median()))
train_df['isAgeKnown'] = train_df['Age'].where(train_df["Age"].isnull(), 1).fillna(0).astype(int)
In [45]:
train_df = pd.concat([train_df, pd.get_dummies(train_df["Sex"])], axis=1)
train_df = pd.concat([train_df, pd.get_dummies(train_df["Embarked"].fillna("embarkedNotKnown"))], axis=1)
train_df.rename(columns={'C': 'Cherbourg','Q': 'Queenstown', 'S': 'Southampton'}, inplace=True)
train_df["FamilySize"]= train_df["SibSp"]+train_df["Parch"]
In [46]:
def extract_Title(row):
    return row["Name"].split(', ' )[1].split(".")[0]
In [47]:
train_df["Title"] = train_df.apply(extract_Title,axis=1)
train_df = pd.concat([train_df, pd.get_dummies(train_df["Title"])], axis=1)

def extract_Title(row):
    return row["Name"].split(', ' )[1].split(".")[0]
In [69]:
submit_df = pd.read_csv(open(working_directory+"./data/test.csv", 'r'))
submit_df['AgeMean'] = submit_df['Age'].fillna((submit_df['Age'].mean()))
submit_df['AgeMed'] = submit_df['Age'].fillna((submit_df['Age'].median()))
submit_df['isAgeKnown'] = submit_df['Age'].where(submit_df["Age"].isnull(), 1).fillna(0).astype(int)
submit_df = pd.concat([submit_df, pd.get_dummies(submit_df["Sex"])], axis=1)
submit_df = pd.concat([submit_df, pd.get_dummies(submit_df["Embarked"].fillna("embarkedNotKnown"))], axis=1)
submit_df.rename(columns={'C': 'Cherbourg','Q': 'Queenstown', 'S': 'Southampton'}, inplace=True)
submit_df["FamilySize"]= submit_df["SibSp"]+submit_df["Parch"]
submit_df["Title"] = submit_df.apply(extract_Title,axis=1)
submit_df = pd.concat([submit_df, pd.get_dummies(submit_df["Title"])], axis=1)
submit_df['Fare'].fillna((submit_df['Fare'].mean()), inplace=True)

from sklearn import preprocessing
submit_df['Age_scaled'] = preprocessing.scale(submit_df['AgeMed'])
submit_df['FamilySize_scaled'] = preprocessing.scale(submit_df['FamilySize'])
submit_df['Pclass_scaled'] = preprocessing.scale(submit_df['Pclass'])
